        Month 1777 : 1777 Timothy Mix serves with (Captain Jonathan Brown’s Co. in the Battalion of Artillery commanded by Col. John Lamb) as a Sergeant
        July 1777 : A Company Muster Roll dated __ July 1777 has remarks “prisoner” (0860.jpg)
        October 1777 : 6 Oct 1777 taken prisoner at the Storming (or Battle) of Fort Montgomery
section Year 4
        Month 1778 : 1778 Timothy Mix serves with (Captain Jonathan Brown’s Co., Colonel John Lamb’s Regiment of Artillery) as a Sergeant
        April 1778 : Timothy Mix is returned around April 1778 from being a prisoner
        September 1778 : 12 Sep 1778 He is promoted from a Sergt. to a 2nd Lieut. on Sepr 12, 1778 in this Compy
    section Year 5
        Month 1779 : 1779 Timothy Mix serves with (Captain Jonathan Brown’s Co., Colonel John Lamb’s Regiment of Artillery) as a Sergeant then 2nd Lieutenant (his rank is updated several months after perhaps being given a field promotion)
        December 1779 : On command Gen’l Poors Brigade starting December 1779 : Doctor Timothy Mix dies 15 Dec 1779 
    section Year 6
        Month 1780 : 1780 Timothy Mix serves with (Captain Joseph Thomas’ Company in the 2d Regiment of Artillery commanded by Col. John Lamb) as a 2nd Lieutenant
        Month 1780 : On command Gen’l Poors Brigade since December 1779
        August 1780 : On command West Point between February and August 1780
    section Year 7
        Month 1781 : 1781 Timothy Mix serves with (Captain Joseph Thomas’ Company in the 2d Regiment of Artillery commanded by Col. John Lamb) as a 2nd Lieutenant
        October 1781 : Timothy the youngest is named as a British prisoner who was captured from the “privateer schooner Young Cromwell”, captured in October 1781. : Timothy the youngest died on an unknown date between capture and April 1782.
    section Year 8
